A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 11, 2025, as Omega Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Inc. was founded on November 17, 1911, on the
3 campus of Howard University, making it the first international fraternal organization founded
4 at a Historically Black College or University; and
5 WHEREAS, the fraternity has four founders—three undergraduate students—Edgar Amos
6 Love, Oscar James Cooper, and Frank Coleman, along with their faculty advisor, Ernest
7 Everett Just; and
8 WHEREAS, the fraternity has four cardinal principles, which are Manhood, Scholarship,
9 Perseverance, and Uplift; and
10 WHEREAS, the name Omega Psi Phi was derived from the initials of the Greek phrase
11 meaning "friendship is essential to the soul," which was selected as the fraternity's motto; and
12 WHEREAS, there are over 250,000 members globally and over 750 chapters throughout the
13 United States, Canada, Mexico, Korea, Japan, China, Ghana, United Kingdom, Bahamas, and
14 Dominican Republic; and
