15 WHEREAS, the Georgia State Organization was established in 1963 and is composed of
16 over 10,000 members and 46 chapters; it provides service in 40 counties throughout the State
17 of Georgia and 16 colleges and universities including Historically Black Colleges and
18 Universities; and
19 WHEREAS, the Omega Psi Phi Fraternity, Inc. International Headquarters is located in
20 DeKalb County, Georgia; and
21 WHEREAS, the fraternity has 12 mandated programs consisting of fatherhood training and
22 youth mentoring, supporting STEM, providing scholarships to high schools seniors and
23 college students, conducting talent hunts to showcase their talents through the arts,
24 facilitating career development workshops, promoting medical and health awareness, and
25 other civic programs including voter registration, education, and mobilization; and
26 WHEREAS, there are many Omega men recognized for their leadership in various industries
27 nationally and internationally, including: The Honorable Hank Johnson, congressman of
28 Georgia's 4th Congressional District; Dr. M. Brian Blake, president of Georgia State
29 University; Dr. Kevin James, president of Morris Brown College; Sheriff Gregory D.
30 Countryman, sheriff of Muscogee County; Sheriff Craig Owens, sheriff of Cobb County; Fitz
31 Johnson, public service commissioner for District 3; Scott Hamilton, police chief of Austell,
32 Georgia; Omari Crawford, representative of House District 89; David Sampson,
33 representative of House District 153; and former Dean of the House Calvin Smyre, just to
34 name a few.
35 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
36 the members of this body commend the State of Georgia Organization Omega Psi Phi
